up|49|NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Stan did well to pass in the first round. Some might bid 2N, but he is a bit weak for that. And Sandy did well to reopen with a double despite having only 2 diamonds.|
PG| ***** 26 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The reason being, although negative doubles are a terrific convention, once in a while responder has a penalty double but responder can't double the overcall, because double by Stan would be negative.|
PG| ***** 27 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Therefore, when it goes 1x-overcall-P-P-?, opener with shortness in the overcalled suit, should strain to reopen with a double. It takes into account the possibility that partner might like to convert it to penalty. Such should have been the case on this hand. Stan should just pass. He has spade length and strength and an outside Ace besides.|
PG| ***** 28 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|I am likely to go down. It is quite possible I will be down 2 or 3, and their side can't make anything. One thing I have noticed is, although many of my students have embraced my philosophy of "bid early bid often" which is normally a good thing. They don't have a good feel as to when it is right to defend.|
PG| ***** 29 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Basically, if you have length in the opponents suit, especially if your length is behind the long suit, as on this hand and shortness in pard's suit the hand could easily be a misfit.|
PG| ***** 30 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|And when the hand is a misfit, you want to defend, not declare. Granted, it is possible that EW have an 8-card or even 9-card diamond fit and that means the hand is not a misfit. But, with long trumps and 3 tricks, doubling will work out better most of the time. I will be down 2 or 3.|
PG| ***** 31 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|I will probably take 1 diamond tricks and perhaps 2 or 3 spade tricks. I might get another trick somewhere, but 5 tricks is down 3.|
