NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|And I play (although most experts again disagree) that if no suit is established, the key card suit is the last suit bid. In this case it would be diamonds. Not perfect, but again unambiguous. To me, unambiguous auctions are more important than perfect auctions. When I play with my regular partners, we rarely have misunderstandings because we have very clear agreements. I am just giving my opinion, which I admit is different from most teachers and experts.|
