qx||ht|b|CP|4|CS|1|FP|2|at|^-{    A Synopsis on Transfer to Minors    }
^-|CP||FP||CS||HT|d|AT|^B@2Transfer to minors after a 1N open comes in different flavors. |
PG| ***** 220 ***** |


AT|

In the simple version, which is what I recommend most of my students to use, 2S by responder forces notrumper to bid 3C. Responder will pass when he/she has clubs. With diamonds responder correct the 3C to 3D. This simple version lets your side play in 3C or 3D, but has no way of distinguishing whether or not opener has good support for the minor. It is generally used by responder with weak hands where one of the minors are 6+ cards and no better bid is available.|
PG| ***** 221 ***** |


AT|

If we were playing 4-suit Jacoby transfers, then 2S is a club transfer and 2N is a diamond transfer. I do not recommend this for most people because it is too easy to forget 2N is a diamond transfer. Regardless, playing 4-suit transfers, responder bids 2S. Notrumper has 2 choices of bids -- 2N says I "|CP|8|AT|like it|CP||AT|" clubs, and 3C says I "|CP||AT|don't like it|CP||AT|" clubs.|
PG| ***** 222 ***** |


AT|

You "like" clubs if you have if you have one of the top 3 honors (@CA, @CK, or @CQ)

2 or even 3 with one of the top 3 honors (@CA, @CK, or @CQ). The reason for that is, in the case where responder wants to bid 3N if their long club suit is running, their long suit often contains 2 of the top 3 (such as KQxxxx). If opener has the other top honor, then the suit is running. If he doesn't, then it is not running.|
PG| ***** 223 ***** |


AT|

So, on the hand we just had, since I do not hold the A, K, or Q of clubs, playing 4-suit transfers, I should bid 3C over 2S, as I did-don't like it. Now 3N turns out not to be a bad contract, but it will not make against best defense. Say West leads a spade. East should put up the SJ. When South starts playing clubs, West must duck twice. Now, South can never get to the board to run clubs because there are no entries (the SQ is behind the SA).|
PG| ***** 224 ***** |


AT|

2N is used by responder when the diamonds being transferred. 1N-P-2N is transfer to diamonds. With one of the top 3 diamond honors (@DA, @DK, or @DQ)the notrumper bids 3C-like it, and 3D-don't like it when the hand does meet the said requirements.|
